com.noctarius.borabora.builder.encoder.semantictag

Interface TimestampBuilder


  • public interface TimestampBuilder
    The TimestampBuilder interface is designed to be used with the TagSupport API.

    To use the builder, a GraphBuilder instance is required. The following example shows how to retrieve and use the builder's instance:

         GraphBuilder graphBuilder = writer.newGraphBuilder( output );
     graphBuilder.putTag(
         TagSupport.semanticTag( TimestampBuilder.class ).putTimestamp( timestamp )
             .endSemanticTag() ).finishStream();

      • putTimestamp

        TagBuilder putTimestamp(Instant timestamp)
        Writes the given Instant value as a timestamp semantic tag. The timestamp value is transformed to an long value first, then written. The returned TagBuilder instance must be used to finalize the building by calling TagBuilder.endSemanticTag().
        Parameters:
        timestamp - the Instant value to write as a timestamp
        Returns:
        the semantic tag finalizing TagBuilder
